The paper deals with the implementation of regular expression matchers, which is a topic that falls under programming languages (cs.PL) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of operational semantics to formalize the implementation technique also suggests a software engineering (cs.SE) perspective. The paper also discusses the use of parallelism, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of logic in computer science (cs.LO) and architecture (cs.AR).
